description: President Trump's 50% tariffs on foreign steel and aluminum took effect Wednesday. Meanwhile, Mr. Trump is expecting to speak with Chinese President Xi Jinping later this week about trade. CBS News MoneyWatch correspondent Kelly O'Grady breaks down the latest economic data, while CBS News' Natalie Brand has the latest updates from the White House.
title: What to expect as Trump's steep tariffs take effect

description: It had not been thought possible that such tiny, weak stars could provide the conditions needed to form and host huge planets.
title: Massive planet discovered orbiting tiny star, puzzling scientists

description: Elon Musk calls President Trump's budget bill a "disgusting abomination"; Pride organizations report funding shortfalls as companies pull back on DEI initiatives.
title: 6/4: CBS Morning News

description: Companies are pulling back Pride Month marketing this year amid President Trump's executive orders targeting diversity, equity and inclusion initiatives. Ad Age senior reporter Adrianne Pasquarelli joins "CBS Morning News" with more.
title: Pride marketing toned down this year amid Trump's DEI crackdown

description: Charlene Kaye's musical parodies are racking up millions of views. But her story runs deeper.
title: How Charlene Kaye is rewriting the rules of pop

description: Billionaire Elon Musk, a close ally of President Trump, called Mr. Trump's massive budget bill "a disgusting abomination" amid estimates that it could raise the deficit by billions. While top Congressional Republicans disagree, critics — including some Republicans — have expressed concern about the national debt while Democrats say it slashes Medicaid and food stamp funding.
title: President Trump's budget bill faces hurdles as Elon Musk calls it "a disgusting abomination"

description: Charlene Kaye, a classically trained musician-turned-comedian, has gone viral for her satirical takes on pop stars like Taylor Swift and Lady Gaga, blending musical theory, internet wit and the tension of growing up with a "tiger mom."
title: Charlene Kaye talks music and going viral with pop parodies

description: Thirty years after ending four decades of Democratic control in the House, former Speaker Newt Gingrich joins "CBS Mornings" to discuss his new book "Trump's Triumph: America's Greatest Comeback," and the future of the Republican Party.
title: Newt Gingrich reflects on GOP legacy and Trump's political comeback

description: Cynthia Erivo joins "CBS Mornings" to discuss hosting the 78th Annual Tony Awards, her behind-the-scenes preparations and what audiences can expect from Sunday night's show.
title: Cynthia Erivo talks Tony Awards preparation as she prepares to host

description: The bodies of three missing girls were found in Washington. Their father, 32-year-old Travis Decker, is suspected of killing them. The search continues for Decker, who is wanted for three counts of murder and kidnapping, police said.
title: Three missing girls found dead in Washington, search continues for father suspected of killing them

description: All week, join CBS Mornings Deals for a very special "summer of savings" event. Visit cbsdeals.com to take advantage of these exclusive deals today. CBS earns commissions on purchases made through cbsdeals.com.
title: Exclusive discounts from CBS Mornings Deals

description: The tomatoes, recalled for potential salmonella contamination, were shipped to Georgia, North Carolina and South Carolina.
title: Tomato recall affecting multiple states elevated to highest risk warning by FDA

description: Defense Secretary Pete Hegseth has issued an order to rename the USNS Harvey Milk. A Defense Department spokesperson says the timing during Pride Month is intentional.
title: Pentagon plans to rename ship honoring gay rights icon Harvey Milk

description: The Gaza Humanitarian Foundation says it is pausing aid operations to improve its work. This comes after reports and witnesses emerged detailing violence and deaths at distribution centers. CBS News' Imtiaz Tyab reports.
title: Controversial Gaza aid group pauses operations after reports of deaths, violence

description: New video appears to show how Mohamed Soliman attacked a group of protesters with Molotov cocktails in Boulder, Colorado. This comes as his family remains in ICE custody and faces deportation after the attack. CBS News' Jason Allen reports.
title: New video emerges of Boulder attack, suspect's family faces deportation

description: The controversial Gaza Humanitarian Foundation has halted its work for a day and is asking Israel to reduce the risks for Palestinians seeking access to its sites.
title: U.S.-backed Gaza aid group pauses work amid reported killings

description: Lee Jae-myung was officially sworn in as South Korea's new president. The liberal candidate defeated Kim Moon Soo after the nation saw its highest voter turnout numbers in over 20 years, according to data. CBS News foreign correspondent Anna Coren has more.
title: New South Korean president vows peace with North Korea, better China relationship

description: Here's what experts say homebuyers can realistically expect to happen with mortgage rates in the coming months.
title: Will mortgage rates fall after the Fed's June meeting?

description: President Trump has not yet commented on Elon Musk's social media post about the Republican budget bill moving through Congress, which came days after the entrepreneur departed his White House post. CBS News' Ed O'Keefe reports on how Musk's influence may affect the president's moves.
title: Could Trump's relationship with Musk sour after his budget bill criticism?

description: A former Los Angeles InterContinental Hotel security guard testified that Sean "Diddy" Combs paid him $100,000 for the security video that showed Combs attacking his ex-girlfriend, Cassie Ventura. CBS News' Katrina Kaufman has the latest on the Combs trial.
title: Sean "Diddy" Combs paid $100,000 for video of Cassie beating, former hotel security guard says

description: Republican lawmakers are responding to Elon Musk's comments labeling the budget bill in Congress a "disgusting abomination." CBS News' Taurean Small reports from Capitol Hill.
title: How Republicans are reacting to Musk's budget bill condemnation

description: The judge in Karen Read's trial denied the defense's request for a mistrial over the use of dog DNA evidence. Read is accused of hitting and killing John O'Keefe, her boyfriend, in 2022. The defense has claimed O'Keefe was attacked by a dog and then beaten to death by others at a house party.
title: Judge denies defense's request for a mistrial in Karen Read case

description: A hiker was discovered dead near the summit of Maine's highest peak Tuesday, after he and his daughter went missing. The daughter has not been found.
title: Hiker found dead, daughter still missing on Maine's highest mountain

description: After nearly a decade, McDonald's announced its Snack Wrap will return to its menu permanently next month. It's the latest move by a fast food chain to lure consumers back. CBS News MoneyWatch correspondent Kelly O'Grady breaks down what to know.
title: McDonald's returning Snack Wrap to its menu as businesses battle over consumers

description: Widespread flash flooding forced officials in Kansas to declare a state of emergency, with crews in Wichita making over 100 water rescues. Meanwhile, the system also triggered a tornado near Kansas City. CBS News' Rob Marciano has the latest.
title: Over 100 water rescues made in Wichita, Kansas, as severe storms slam the Midwest

description: Students at Milford High School in Massachusetts staged a walkout Monday to protest the arrest of their classmate, Marcelo Gomes Da Silva, as part of an ICE operation over the weekend. Officials say Gomes Da Silva was not their intended target. CBS News' Lilia Luciano reports.
title: Protests over arrest of undocumented Massachusetts high school student now in ICE custody

description: Powerful storms bring record rainfall to parts of the Midwest, causing severe flash flooding and forcing more than 100 water rescues. Also, Elon Musk calls President Trump's tax cut and spending bill an "abomination" and bashes everyone who voted for it. All that and all that matters in today's Eye Opener.
title: Eye Opener: Powerful storms bring record rainfall to parts of the Midwest

description: President Trump's steel and aluminum tariffs have officially doubled to 50%, and American manufacturing experts are warning that the costs will be passed down in the supply chain, possibly raising prices for consumers. CBS News' Natalie Brand reports.
title: Trump's tariffs on steel, aluminum officially double

description: The family of Sarah Milgrim reflect on her life and career with the Israeli Embassy and watching her "love blossom" with her boyfriend Yaron Lischinsky after the couple was killed outside the Capital Jewish Museum in Washington, D.C. last month.
title: Family of Sarah Milgrim describes her courage, blossoming love before D.C. shooting

description: Scientists have unlocked one of the solar system's many secrets from an unexpected source: a planetarium show.
title: Fluke discovery at planetarium sheds light on mysterious cosmic cloud

description: Republican tax bill requires both parents to have a Social Security number to qualify for the Child Tax Credit, a policy shift that would make millions of kids ineligible.
title: Millions of kids could lose the Child Tax Credit under GOP budget bill

description: The U.S. doubled steel and aluminum tariffs to 50%, casting a pall on a gathering of OECD ministers as President Trump's intensifying trade war weighs on the world economy.
title: U.S. doubles tariffs on steel and aluminum to 50%

description: A family man abruptly vanishes. Police tie his disappearance to a monstrous plot for revenge. "48 Hours" contributor Natalie Morales reports.
title: Who Took Our Dad? The Abduction of Ray Wright
